## 🚨 CRITICAL BUGS (Production-Breaking)

### 1. `setExamStarted` called before declaration — Ordering Bug
**File:** [tests/[id]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/siddh/OneDrive/Desktop/mock%20app/client/src/app/dashboard/tests/%5Bid%5D/page.tsx#L63)

```tsx
// Line 63 — inside checkStatus() useCallback:
setExamStarted(false); // state declared at line 146 AFTER this callback
```
`setExamStarted` is referenced inside `checkStatus` (declared via `useCallback` at line 56) but is only defined by `useState` at line 146. While React hooks execute in stable order, this is a **severe code smell** and any refactor will crash. Declare `examStarted` state at the TOP of the component, before `checkStatus`.

