## 🔐 SECURITY VULNERABILITIES

### S1. JSON Body Limit = 50MB — DoS Risk
**File:** [index.ts](file:///c:/Users/siddh/OneDrive/Desktop/mock%20app/server/src/index.ts#L25)

```ts
app.use(express.json({ limit: '50mb' }));
app.use(express.urlencoded({ limit: '50mb', extended: true }));
```
Any endpoint accepts 50MB payloads, enabling easy memory exhaustion attacks. Reduce to `1mb` globally; use a specific limit only on the bulk upload route.

---

### S2. Dev-Mode Google Auth Backdoor
**File:** [auth.controller.ts](file:///c:/Users/siddh/OneDrive/Desktop/mock%20app/server/src/controllers/auth.controller.ts#L123)

```ts
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development' && credential.startsWith('dev-mock-google-')) {
    // login/create user with ANY email, zero validation
}
```
If `NODE_ENV` is not explicitly set to `'production'`, this backdoor is active in deployed environments. Anyone can authenticate as any email address.

---

### S3. In-Memory Rate Limiter Has Multiple Weaknesses
**File:** [rateLimit.middleware.ts](file:///c:/Users/siddh/OneDrive/Desktop/mock%20app/server/src/middleware/rateLimit.middleware.ts)

- Resets on every server restart — brute-force restarts bypass it
- Does not work with multiple server instances (no shared Redis store)
- Old IP entries are **never cleaned up** — slow memory leak
- 100 requests / 15 min is very permissive for auth endpoints

Replace with `express-rate-limit` + Redis store.

---

### S4. No CSRF Protection
Cookie-based auth with `httpOnly: true` is used, but no CSRF tokens are validated. Malicious third-party sites can trigger state-changing API calls (logout, submit result) from authenticated sessions.

---

### S5. Biased Random Shuffle in Custom Tests
**File:** [test.controller.ts](file:///c:/Users/siddh/OneDrive/Desktop/mock%20app/server/src/controllers/test.controller.ts#L218)

```ts
finalQuestions = questions.sort(() => 0.5 - Math.random()).slice(0, questionCount);
```
`Array.sort` with a random comparator produces a **statistically biased shuffle** — certain question orderings appear far more often than others. Use the Fisher-Yates algorithm.

---

### S6. New Password Not Validated on Reset
**File:** [auth.controller.ts](file:///c:/Users/siddh/OneDrive/Desktop/mock%20app/server/src/controllers/auth.controller.ts#L222)

```ts
const hashedPassword = await bcrypt.hash(newPassword, 10); // no length check
```
A user can reset to a 1-character password. Add `min(8)` validation via Zod or a manual check.

---

### S7. Debug Scripts in the Server Directory
Files in `/server/`: `debug_delete.js`, `debug_tests.js`, `inspect_tests.js`, `inspect_tests_v2.js`, `SIDD.PY`, `practice.cpp`

These expose database logic and should not live in the server root. The `.py` and `.cpp` files are entirely misplaced.

